---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — What's My Time Worth"
  description="A small tool for a big idea: your salary is not what your time is worth."
>
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <a href="/" class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-mute hover:text-blood">
      &larr; Back to the calculator
    </a>

    <h1 class="font-display font-light text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-tightest mt-8 mb-10">
      About
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        This is a single-purpose calculator that asks a simple question: when
        you subtract everything your job actually costs you, and divide by
        every hour it actually takes, what's your real hourly wage?
      </p>

      <p>
        The answer is almost always smaller than the number on your offer
        letter. Sometimes a lot smaller.
      </p>

      <p>
        The concept comes from the 1992 book <em>Your Money or Your Life</em>
        by Vicki Robin and Joe Dominguez. The math has been around for
        thirty years. The internet has been surprisingly bad at putting it
        into a tool that loads fast, doesn't ask for your email, and lets
        you type in what you're about to buy to see what it actually costs
        you in time.
      </p>

      <p>
        That's what this is.
      </p>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-ink/10 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-2xl tracking-tightest mb-4">
          No, seriously, no signup
        </h2>
        <p>
          Every calculation runs in your browser. We don't store your
          numbers, send them anywhere, or try to upsell you on a
          subscription. If you want, you can look at the source.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-ink/10 mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-2xl tracking-tightest mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Corrections, complaints, or calculator ideas:{' '}
          <a
            href="mailto:hello@whatsmytimeworth.com"
            class="underline decoration-blood decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-blood"
          >
            hello@whatsmytimeworth.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-ink/10">
      <a href="/" class="btn-primary">Back to the calculator</a>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Base>
